A BILL TO BE ENTITLED
AN ACT
1 To amend an Act to amend, consolidate, create, revise, and supersede the several Acts
2 incorporating the City of Pembroke, approved March 28, 1985 (Ga. L. 1985, p. 4846), as
3 amended, so as to provide for four-year terms for the mayor and city council members; to
4 provide for elections; to provide for the current terms of city officers to continue; to repeal
5 conflicting laws; and for other purposes.
6 BE IT ENACTED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF GEORGIA:
7 SECTION 1.
8 An Act to amend, consolidate, create, revise, and supersede the several Acts incorporating
9 the City of Pembroke, approved March 28, 1985 (Ga. L. 1985, p. 4846), as amended, is
10 amended by revising Section 4 as follows:
11 "Section 4.
12 The next general election for mayor and five city council members shall be held on the first
13 Tuesday in November, 2027, at which time a mayor and five city council members shall
14 be elected to take office on the second Monday in January, 2028, for a term of four years
15 and until their successors are elected and qualified. Thereafter, successors shall be elected
16 at the municipal general election which shall be held every four years on the first Tuesday
